The paper proposes a novel CNN-based framework for trajectory prediction, which involves modeling spatial and temporal interactions in an input-aware manner. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV) for the spatial modeling aspect, machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the use of deep learning techniques, robotics (cs.RO) for the application of trajectory prediction in autonomous systems, and social and information networks (cs.SI) for the graph-based modeling approach.
